question: Isabella has 11 jars of chocolate chips in her storage room. Each jar of chocolate chips can decorate 13 muffins. Isabella wants to bake enough muffins to use up all of her chocolate chips. If each rack holds 13 muffins, how many racks worth of muffins should she bake?
answer:
She has enough chocolate chips for 11 * 13 = <<11*13=143>>143 muffins.
She needs 143 / 13 = <<143/13=11>>11 racks to bake all of the muffins.
#### 11
